Warren Street Methodist Episcopal Church, also known as Warren Street United Methodist Church, is a historic Methodist church located at 201 South Warren Street in Warrensburg, Johnson County, Missouri. It was built in 1898â€“1899, and is a one-story, Late Gothic Revival style orange-tinted brick building.  It features a square entrance tower with a concave dome and a gabled cornice.  It was erected by a local African-American congregation.
It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1996.
